# Implementation Plan - Project AssetFlow

Build a modern, enterprise-grade Single Page Application (SPA) for asset rental management, designed specifically for integration within Microsoft Teams.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The app will be built using **React + TypeScript + Vite** for a professional modular structure.
> We will follow the **Microsoft Fluent Design System** (Teams Blue #5B5FC7, minimalist gray/white aesthetics).

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] Project AssetFlow Directory Structure
We will initialize a new Vite project in `02_Workspace/Project_AssetFlow`.

#### [NEW] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/cfpcl/OneDrive/Desktop/AI_OS_HQ/02_Workspace/Project_AssetFlow/src/index.css)
- Implement Fluent Design tokens:
  - Primary: `#5B5FC7` (Teams Blue)
  - Backgrounds: `#F5F5F5`, `#FFFFFF`
  - Typography: `Segoe UI`, system-ui
- Define layout utilities for Tabs and Grid.

#### [NEW] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/cfpcl/OneDrive/Desktop/AI_OS_HQ/02_Workspace/Project_AssetFlow/src/App.tsx)
- State management for `assets` and `rentals` (using provided Mock Data).
- Tab navigation logic (Rental Form / Dashboard / Inventory).

#### [NEW] [RentalForm.tsx](file:///c:/Users/cfpcl/OneDrive/Desktop/AI_OS_HQ/02_Workspace/Project_AssetFlow/src/components/RentalForm.tsx)
- Smart form with auto-fill logic.
- Validation for required fields.
